JOB  DESCRIPTION

A  Senior Officer / Assistant Head in Infocomm Cluster of SERC is required to  support the strategising and managing of A*STAR뭩 R&amp;D initiatives in digital  technologies, such as:
 AI  and Data Science
 Communications  and Internet-of-Things
 Digital  trust technologies (eg. privacy preservation and distributed ledger  technologies)
 Cybersecurity
 Digital  Twinning and Modelling &amp; Simulations
The  officer will be part of a dynamic Infocomm Cluster team which shapes public  sector research and innovation to deliver economic and societal outcomes for  Singapore through:
 Strategic  planning, coordination, and collaborations in digital technology R&amp;D with  Ministries &amp; Public Agencies partners, Research Institutes, Institutes of  Higher Learning, and industry sectors
 Long-term  R&amp;D planning and stakeholder engagements that shape and contribute directly  to the national R&amp;D agenda
 Technology  Foresighting and Masterplanning to optimise R&amp;D investment portfolio and  ensure alignment with national priorities
 R&amp;D  programme strategy development and design, which entails convening relevant  public agencies, enterprises, and research entities (within A*STAR and from  Institutes of Higher Learning) into collaboration programmes and securing  necessary management support and resources for programme  execution
 R&amp;D  programme execution and management, including planning for subsequent technology  translation and commercialisation
 Strategic  development and reviews of digital technology capabilities in A*STAR Research  Institutes
 Research  proposals evaluation, project reviews and grant management

JOB  REQUIREMENTS

 Background  in Engineering, IT or Computer Science, with preferably 2 or more years of  working experience in these fields
 Ability  to think strategically and analyse issues from different  angles
 Knowledge  in a broad range of digital technologies, the digital industry, their trends,  challenges, and potentials
 Passion  in shaping research and innovation in digital technologies to bring about  economic and societal outcomes for Singapore
 Proactive  learning attitude, attention to details and  results-oriented
 Comfortable  with delivering outcomes in complex environment within challenging  timelines